x4freetext: Three PIPS detectors for Nuclear Reaction Analysis
measurements and one Si PIN detector at 160 degrees for
A three-layered sample of 500 nm W on Si, with a Be
thin film on top of the W. The thin Be film
deposition was performed by the thermionic vacuum arc
method using ITER grade quality Be (>99% pure Be, <1%
BeO, and <0.1% C). The Be areal density (nBe)
obtained is nBe=(19.2+-1.4) x10E17 atoms/cm2, which
corresponds to a thickness of (156+-11.3) nm
